<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>The Bookish Circle - American Bookworm Insights</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-image: url("/img/background.jpg"); /* Optional background image */
            background-size: cover;
            background-repeat: no-repeat;
            background-position: center;
            background-attachment: fixed;
            color: #333; /* Darker text for contrast */
        }

        /* Header */
        header {
            background-color: #384b38; /* Night Blue */
            color: #fff;
            padding: 20px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 3em;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            letter-spacing: 3px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            font-weight: bold;
            background-color: #384b38;
            color: #fff;
            padding: 20px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        /* Navigation */
        nav {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-around;
            padding: 10px 0;
            background-color: #c89666; /* Light Yellow */
            box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

            nav a {
                color: #384b38; /* Night Blue */
                text-decoration: none;
                padding: 10px 20px;
                border-radius: 5px;
                transition: background-color 0.3s, color 0.3s;
                font-weight: bold;
            }

                nav a:hover {
                    background-color: #c1a77a; /* Lighter Yellow */
                    color: #fff;
                }

                nav a.active {
                    background-color: #384b38; /* Night Blue */
                    color: #fff;
                }

        /* Main Content */
        main {
            padding: 20px;
        }

        /* American Bookworms Unite! Section */
        .hero {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            margin-bottom: 40px;
        }

            .hero h2 {
                font-size: 2em;
                margin-bottom: 10px;
            }

            .hero img {
                width: 50%;
                margin-bottom: 20px;
            }

        /* Book Insights Section */
        .insights {
            display: flex;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            justify-content: space-between;
            gap: 20px;
        }

        .insight {
            background-color: #e1b382; /* Sand Tan */
            color: #333; /* Darker text for contrast */
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            width: calc(48% - 20px); /* Adjusted width for each insight */
            max-width: calc(48% - 20px); /* Adjusted max-width for responsiveness */
            box-sizing: border-box;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

            .insight h3 {
                font-weight: bold;
                margin-bottom: 10px;
            }

            .insight p {
                font-size: 1em;
            }

        /* Call to Action Section */
        .cta {
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

            .cta button {
                padding: 15px 30px;
                font-size: 1.2em;
                background-color: #2d545e; /* Night Blue */
                color: #fff;
                border: none;
                border-radius: 5px;
                cursor: pointer;
                transition: background-color 0.3s;
            }

                .cta button:hover {
                    background-color: #384b38; /* Darker Night Blue */
                }

        /* Discussion Section */
        .discussion {
            border-top: 1px solid #ddd;
            padding-top: 20px;
        }

            .discussion h3 {
                font-size: 1.5em;
                margin-bottom: 10px;
            }

        /* Footer */
        footer {
            background-color: #384b38;
            color: #fff;
            padding: 20px;
            text-align: center;
        }

            footer a {
                color: #fff;
                text-decoration: none;
                transition: color 0.3s;
            }

                footer a:hover {
                    color: #c1a77a; /* Lighter Yellow */
                }

        /* Social Media Icons (Optional) */
        .social-icons {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            margin-top: 10px;
        }

            .social-icons a {
                margin: 0 10px;
            }

    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <header>
        <h1>The Bookish Circle</h1>
    </header>

    <nav>
        <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Index">Home</a>
        <a asp-controller="About" asp-action="Index">About Us</a>
        <a asp-controller="FeaturedBooks" asp-action="Index">Featured Books</a>
        <a asp-controller="Membership" asp-action="Index">Membership</a>
        <a asp-controller="Book Insights" asp-action="Index">BookInsights</a>
        <a asp-controller="SignUp" asp-action="Index">Sign up</a>
    </nav>

    <main>
        <section class="hero">
            <h2>American Bookworms Unite!</h2>
            <img src="/img/bookworm.jpg" alt="Image of a bookworm">
            <p>Intriguing Book Statistics Reveal What Americans are Reading</p>
        </section>

        <section class="insights">
            <div class="insight">
                <h3>Nation of Bookworms</h3>
                <img src="/img/bookstack.jpg" alt="Image of a stack of books">
                <p>The US takes the crown for reading the most, with a whopping 39% reporting over 20 books read in 2022!</p>
            </div>

            <div class="insight">
                <h3>Planning to Read Even More</h3>
                <img src="/img/future-reading.jpg" alt="Image of someone reading with a futuristic background">
                <p>Good news! Americans are aiming to surpass their reading goals in 2023, with 61% planning to crack open more books than ever before.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="insight">
                <h3>Favorite Genres</h3>
                <img src="/img/genres.jpg" alt="Image of a bookshelf with different colored sections">
                <p>History, mystery, and biography reign supreme, captivating 7% more American readers than the global average.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="insight">
                <h3>Paperbacks and Kindles Rule</h3>
                <img src="/img/paperback-kindle.jpg" alt="Image of a paperback book and a Kindle">
                <p>While the digital age is upon us, Americans wciąż (vitch) cling to the comfort of paperbacks (34%) and adore their Kindles (29%). (That's "still" in Polish, for all the bookworm linguists out there!)</p>
            </div>

            <div class="insight">
                <h3>The Right Length Matters, But Not Too Short</h3>
                <img src="/img/book-length.jpg" alt="Image of a person holding a book and measuring it">
                <p>Writers rejoice! The majority of readers (84%) find books to be just the perfect length, striking a happy medium between gripping narrative and concise storytelling.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="insight">
                <h3>A Diverse Reading Age Range</h3>
                <img src="/img/diverse-readers.jpg" alt="Image of a group of people of different ages reading">
                <p>Contrary to some beliefs, readers come in all ages! The survey revealed a healthy spread across demographics, with a notable showing from those 5
            </div>

            <div class="insight">
                <h3>Women Lead the Reading Charge</h3>
                <img src="/img/women-reading.jpg" alt="Image of women reading">
                <p>The survey found that 67% of American readers identify as women, solidifying the trend of women cherishing the written word.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="cta">
            <h3>Let the Discussion Begin!</h3>
            <p>What are your favorite genres? Do you prefer the feel of a physical book or the convenience of an eReader? Share your thoughts in the comments below!</p>
            <button>Explore Our Book Collection</button>
        </section>
    </main>

    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2024 The Bookish Circle</p>
        <a href="#">Contact Us</a>
        <a href="#">Privacy Policy</a>
        <a href="#">Terms of Service</a>

        <div class="social-icons">
            <a href="#"><i class="fab fa-facebook"></i></a>
            <a href="#"><i class="fab fa-twitter"></i></a>
            <a href="#"><i class="fab fa-instagram"></i></a>
        </div>
    </footer>
</body>

</html>
